product_name: GarnierErase It All Makeup Cleansing Balm Vitamin C
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeSustainable PackagingGarnier SkinActive Erase It All Makeup Cleansing Balm Vitamin C cleansing balm is specially formulated with Vitamin C to cleanse and gently remove all types of longwear makeup including eye, lips, face and sunscreen residue.
details: DetailsBenefitsErases all types of makeup cleanses and brightens with Vitamin CMakes the skin look instantly and overtime brighter while leaving skin hydrated for 24 hoursGarnier recommends using Erase It All Makeup Cleansing Balm in the morning and the eveningThis 3 in 1 Makeup Cleansing Balm can also be used as a Mask by applying it to clean skin for 10 minutesItem 2626029How To UseUse in the morning and the evening. To remove makeup and cleanse your skin, massage a generous amount of balm into dry skin using circular motions. Add water to create a milky lather, and rinse clean with warm water. This 3-in-1 Cleansing Balm can also be used as a mask by applying it to clean skin for 10 minutes, 2 to 3 times per week, and rinsing it with warm water.Precautions: Avoid getting in eyes. Rinse eyes thoroughly if contact occurs.IngredientsEthylhexyl Palmitate, Polyethylene, Peg-20 Glyceryl Triisostearate, Butyrospermum Parkii Butter / Shea Butter, Phenoxyethanol, Peg-30 Dipolyhydroxystearate, Simmondsia Chinensis Seed Oil / Jojoba Seed Oil, Caprylyl Glycol, Tocopherol, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Polysorbate 20, Octyldodecanol, Ci 19140 / Yellow 5 Lake, Ppg-26-Buteth-26, Peg-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Aqua / Water / Eau, Citric Acid.
how_to_use: Use in the morning and the evening. To remove makeup and cleanse your skin, massage a generous amount of balm into dry skin using circular motions. Add water to create a milky lather, and rinse clean with warm water. This 3-in-1 Cleansing Balm can also be used as a mask by applying it to clean skin for 10 minutes, 2 to 3 times per week, and rinsing it with warm water.Precautions: Avoid getting in eyes. Rinse eyes thoroughly if contact occurs.

reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Melt on your face oily butter cream. Melts makeup off very well. Leaves skin looking clean and youthful and feeling smooth! For the amount of product you get, the price is great!

reviews.headline: Would not buy again- burns eyes
reviews.comments: This works, but its really greasy. It doesnt come off well (definitely cleanse with a regular cleanser after). It burns my eyes and gets in them in that way that makes everything blurry. There are much better affordable cleansing balms available.

reviews.headline: It performs well
reviews.comments: I was hoping for an economical cleansing balm that worked well and smelled fresh. Will finish this not to waste it - the hunt continues

reviews.headline: Not to be used alone
reviews.comments: This product does remove makeup but is not soluble with warm water so you need another cleanser to remove residual from the balm. Sort of defeats the purpose...

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Melt on your face oily butter cream. Melts makeup off very well. Leaves skin looking clean and youthful and feeling smooth! For the amount of product you get, the price is great! Would be happy to purchase again.

reviews.headline: Pretty good
reviews.comments: This is now my second jar of this, i first bought the blue one which was pretty good it went on creamy and melted all my makeup pretty nicely. I havent tried this yellow one yet, one thing i will say is the smell is not the best but besides that it leaves my skin feeling clean. I also double cleanse, i usually use this then wash off and after go in with my gentle cleanser, and it removed all makeup, every now and then i will use some micellar water after using the balm.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: Absolutely beyond excited to have received this item to try out. It works so good!

reviews.headline: The smell...
reviews.comments:
This product is a good basic cleansing balm. It takes off my makeup but I do have to work it into my skin a little more aggressive and longer. 

The biggest con for me is the smell. I'm a low fragrance/fragrance free person and this made me feel nauseous. It doesn't smell good at all...if you think it's going to smell fruity because it's formulated with vitamin C...sadly it's not like that at all. I'll work through the rest of the balm but will probably not purchase again.

reviews.headline: Worth it!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It melts away makeup especially stubborn mascara and foundation so effortlessly without leaving my skin feeling greasy or stripped. The texture is smooth and gentle, and it rinses off clean with no residue. My skin feels soft, clean, and hydrated after using it. Plus, it has a light, pleasant scent that's not overpowering. Great quality at an affordable price!

reviews.headline: Hate it
reviews.comments: I usually use ponds cold cream but for some reason the bright packaging attracted me. I wish i never bought it. It has a faint mildew smell. Goes on your face nicely like any other balm but literally does nothing to help take the makeup off easily without scrubbing . You need a lot and it stings the eyes. Does not leave your face feeling soft or cleansed. I never write reviews but i had to for this one.

reviews.headline: Hate it
reviews.comments: I usually use ponds cold cream but for some reason the bright packaging attracted me. I wish i never bought it. It has a faint mildew smell. Goes on your face nicely like any other balm but literally does nothing to help take the makeup off easily without scrubbing . You need a lot and it stings the eyes. Does not leave your face feeling soft or cleansed. I never write reviews but i had to for this one.

reviews.headline: this is great
reviews.comments:
I'm usually a cleansing oil type of girl, or I usually just use my foaming gel cleansers 2x to remove my makeup.

but this formula is great, it's very smooth and buttery, but it doesn't leave an oily residue on the skin.  
you also get a big jar for the price.

reviews.headline: DO NOT BUY.
reviews.comments: This is literally the WORST makeup cleansing bomb ive ever tried. It did not even remove any of my mascara and the texture is so weird and thin and hurts to rub on eyes. Also it got clumps of mascara stuck in my eye that has been stuck there now for 3 weeks, i have to go to the doctor to get it removed. Terrible.

reviews.headline: love it!
reviews.comments:
I was looking for a makeup remover that wasn't wipes and came across this in store. First the price is great for the amount your getting, compared it to other balms and you pay more for less. 

my makeup GLIDES off, no fuss no struggle. it also doesn't dry my skin and I haven't gotten breakouts. it washes off so easily I love her. 

will definitely be purchasing again.

reviews.headline: Recommend 100%
reviews.comments: I have been looking for a makeup remover that's not greasy and  I have finally found it!

reviews.headline: Works
reviews.comments: This is my first cleansing balm ive tried and I have sensitive skin so im glad it didnt burn. It removes makeup great but im not sure if ill buy it again. I prefer the garnier micellar water which is my absolute fav.

reviews.headline: Strongly recommend for regular use!!!
reviews.comments: The Garnier Erase It All Makeup Cleansing Balm with  Vitamin C lives up to its name. It took all makeup off, ever single time I used it. It left my skin feeling moisturized and clean. The scent is a definite perk also. Smells SO good and clean. Love this makeup remover.

reviews.headline: It works
reviews.comments: I like the product, didn't rate 5 stars because I do feel the need to remove residue with a rinse off after using it. It worked well on waterproof mascara.  Love Clinique's Take the Day Off but it also needs a rinse afterwards.

reviews.headline: Good product
reviews.comments: This product works well to take off makeup. I found it easy to use and it felt nice going on my skin. It did dry my skin out a little bit moisturizing after is recommended anyway. I did receive this complimentary

faceoff_positive.comments:
I've been using the Erase It All Skin Active Makeup Cleansing Balm for a few weeks now, and it's quickly become an essential part of my skincare routine. This balm does exactly what its name promises‚Äîerasing every trace of makeup with minimal effort.

The texture of the balm is rich and smooth, melting effortlessly into the skin upon application. As soon as it touches your face, it transforms into a silky oil that breaks down even the most stubborn makeup, including waterproof mascara and long-wear foundation. I love how it doesn't tug on my skin; instead, it glides over it, making makeup removal a soothing experience.

One of the standout features of this cleansing balm is how it leaves my skin feeling afterward. Unlike some makeup removers that can leave your skin feeling stripped or dry, the Erase It All balm leaves my skin feeling soft, hydrated, and thoroughly cleansed. It's packed with skin-loving ingredients, so it not only cleanses but also nourishes my skin.

The balm is also fragrance-free, which is great for those with sensitive skin or anyone who prefers their skincare products to be gentle and non-irritating. After rinsing, there's no greasy residue left behind, just clean, comfortable skin.

Overall, the Erase It All Skin Active Makeup Cleansing Balm is a fantastic product that delivers on its promises. It's effective, gentle, and leaves my skin feeling better than before. If you're looking for a makeup remover that does it all, this is definitely worth trying
faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing product

faceoff_negative.comments:
I'm so happy that "drugstore" brands are finally getting with the double cleanse program! I usually use a cleansing oil as my first step to take off my makeup before using a foaming cleanser, but I'm always in the market for a balm because they are less messy and way more convenient for when you are traveling. This was almost as good, if not better that most balms l've tried except for one major issue: when it gets in your eyes (which is inevitable if you're trying to remove eyeliner) it not only creates a film in your eyes making eyesight cloudy for a minute, but it stings! Not horribly, but enough to make the experience not all that enjoyable. A film is not a dealbreaker, all but one balm l've tried does that, which is why l prefer oil, but I've never had a cleansing balm sting my eyes!
Everything else about this product is great: great cleansing performance, very subtle if any, scent, good texture, not messy. I would probably purchase if they made a smaller size for travel, but I would be hesitant to recommend to someone else based on the fact that it burned my non-sensitive eyes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Does a great job but stings my eyes!
